  "prompt": "How should a bedroom be arranged, according to feng shui?",
  "response": "According to feng shui principles, here are some key guidelines for arranging a bedroom:\n\n1. Bed Placement\n- Position the bed against a solid wall\n- Place the bed so you can see the door, but not directly in line with it\n- Avoid placing the bed under a window\n- Do not place the bed under a heavy beam or sloped ceiling\n\n2. Bed Orientation\n- The headboard should face north or east for best energy flow\n- Avoid aligning the bed with the door\n\n3. Space Around the Bed\n- Leave space on both sides of the bed\n- Ensure there's room to walk around the bed\n- Avoid clutter under the bed\n\n4. Room Colors\n- Use calming, neutral colors like soft blues, greens, or earth tones\n- Avoid overly stimulating colors like bright red\n\n5. Decor and Accessories\n- Use pairs of items to promote balance\n- Include soft, rounded shapes\n- Minimize electronic devices\n- Use soft, soothing artwork\n\n6. General Principles\n- Keep the room clean and well-organized\n- Ensure good air circulation\n- Use soft, ambient lighting\n- Remove mirrors facing the bed\n\nFollowing these guidelines can help create a peaceful, harmonious bedroom environment according to feng shui philosophy.",
